---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import SectionHeader from "../components/SectionHeader.astro";
import CanonStages from "../components/CanonStages.astro";
import PathCard from "../components/PathCard.astro";
import RoadmapTimeline from "../components/RoadmapTimeline.astro";
import CtaBand from "../components/CtaBand.astro";
---
<Base>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pt-20 pb-20 md:pt-32 md:pb-28">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-6">NORA Foundation · Canon v0.1.0 · draft-rfc</div>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl md:text-7xl leading-[1.04] tracking-tight text-ink-800 max-w-5xl">
      Verifiable reasoning.<br />
      <span class="text-cardinal-600">Public infrastructure.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-xl leading-relaxed text-ink-600">
      NORA Foundation publishes <strong>Canon</strong> — an open standard for the artifact an AI system issues when a claim has passed through Witness, Findings, Refutation, and Seal. Any recipient can verify a Canon attestation without trusting the issuer.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/canon">Read the Canon →</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/donate">Support the foundation</a>
      <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/NORA-BITSY" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-x-8 gap-y-4 text-sm max-w-3xl">
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Licence</div>
        <div class="text-ink-700 mt-1">CC0 1.0 Universal</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Signature</div>
        <div class="text-ink-700 mt-1">Ed25519 · RFC 8032</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Canonical&shy;ization</div>
        <div class="text-ink-700 mt-1">JCS · RFC 8785</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Status</div>
        <div class="text-ink-700 mt-1">Draft-RFC · open for PR</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-ink-200" />

  <!-- ORIGIN → GENERAL PROBLEM -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
    <SectionHeader
      eyebrow="§1 — Why this exists"
      title="A real use case revealed a general problem."
      lede="NORA was forged in a demanding real-world evidentiary context — a setting where retrieval, interpretation, and provenance all had to be audited by someone other than the system that produced them. That pressure exposed a problem far larger than any one case: modern AI systems emit output that recipients cannot independently verify."
    />

    <div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl">
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-sm text-cardinal-600 mb-2">retrieval without reasoning</div>
        <p class="text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          A vector database returns a ranked list. It cannot explain why each result was ranked where it was, what it missed, or how the answer would change under a slightly different query.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-sm text-cardinal-600 mb-2">generation without provenance</div>
        <p class="text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          A language model produces plausible text. It does not produce a record of which passages it relied on, which inference types were applied, or which facts were asserted without support.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-sm text-cardinal-600 mb-2">signatures without binding</div>
        <p class="text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          A digitally-signed document proves a file was signed. It does not commit the issuer to a specific reasoning chain, an acknowledged set of gaps, or a survived adversarial challenge.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-14 max-w-3xl text-lg text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
      The problem is structural, not cosmetic. It applies wherever a party must rely on an AI system's output without being able to cooperate with — or trust — the system that produced it: evidentiary review, investigative journalism, academic research over private archives, compliance and audit, records-intensive knowledge work. NORA turns the lesson of a concrete case into public infrastructure.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-ink-200" />

  <!-- WHAT NORA DOES -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
    <SectionHeader
      eyebrow="§2 — What NORA does"
      title="Publish the standard. Build the implementation. Support the ecosystem."
    />

    <div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-px bg-ink-200 border border-ink-200">
      <div class="bg-white p-8">
        <div class="font-serif text-2xl text-cardinal-600 mb-3">01</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-3">Publish Canon</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          An open, implementation-neutral specification for verifiable reasoning artifacts. Published under CC0. Amendments by public pull request. No permission required to build against it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-8">
        <div class="font-serif text-2xl text-cardinal-600 mb-3">02</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-3">Build Meridian-Canon</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          The reference implementation — a system that ingests heterogeneous archives, normalizes them, enriches them with a local language model, challenges its own conclusions, and emits sealed, verifiable attestations.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-8">
        <div class="font-serif text-2xl text-cardinal-600 mb-3">03</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-3">Support the ecosystem</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          Independent verifiers. Adversarial review. Domain-specific challenge vocabularies. Grants to outside implementers. The standard is only meaningful if many parties can issue and verify under it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-ink-200" />

  <!-- CANON STAGES -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
    <SectionHeader
      eyebrow="§3 — The Canon"
      title="Four stages. One signed artifact."
      lede="A NORA Attestation is a JSON document produced when a claim has passed through four functions in sequence. The structure is public, implementation-neutral, and inspectable by any recipient without the issuer's cooperation."
    />

    <div class="mt-14">
      <CanonStages compact={true} />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a class="btn" href="/canon">About the Canon →</a>
      <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/NORA-BITSY/nora-canon/blob/main/CANON.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read CANON.md</a>
      <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/NORA-BITSY/nora-canon/blob/main/canon.schema.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JSON schema</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-ink-200" />

  <!-- MERIDIAN-CANON -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
    <SectionHeader
      eyebrow="§4 — The reference implementation"
      title="Meridian-Canon."
      lede="Canon-conformant infrastructure for large, heterogeneous archives where retrieval, interpretation, and provenance must all be auditable. First developed under a demanding real-world archival and evidentiary workload; architected from the beginning to generalize beyond it."
    />

    <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-4">What it does</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-3 text-ink-600">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">1.</span> Ingests heterogeneous sources into one database with cryptographic hashes and chain of custody.</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">2.</span> Extracts structured claims per document via a local language model, with explicit inference types and acknowledged gaps.</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">3.</span> Challenges every claim via a five-stage adversarial harness before sealing.</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">4.</span> Answers natural-language queries with sealed <code>SearchAttestation</code>s. Synthesizes <code>BriefAttestation</code>s for broader evidentiary or editorial products.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-4">Use-case classes</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-600 text-sm">
          <li>· Legal review and evidence preparation</li>
          <li>· Investigative journalism with large source archives</li>
          <li>· Academic research on private corpora</li>
          <li>· Compliance, audit, and regulatory review</li>
          <li>· Institutional and personal records management</li>
          <li>· FOIA and transparency work</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/meridian-canon">About Meridian-Canon →</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/meridian-canon-executive-summary.pdf">Executive summary (PDF)</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-ink-200" />

  <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
    <SectionHeader
      eyebrow="§5 — Who this is for"
      title="Five ways to engage."
    />

    <div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-px bg-ink-200 border border-ink-200">
      <PathCard eyebrow="Donors" title="Support the work"
        body="Fund specification drafting, reference implementations, verifier tooling, adversarial review, and ecosystem grants. Every line of support is traceable to a category of work."
        cta={{ href: "/donate", label: "Donate" }}
      />
      <PathCard eyebrow="Institutional funders" title="Grants and partnerships"
        body="For foundations, labs, civic-tech funders, and corporate philanthropy programs. We welcome multi-year structured support for public-interest infrastructure."
        cta={{ href: "/partners", label: "Partner with us" }}
      />
      <PathCard eyebrow="Contributors" title="Build the ecosystem"
        body="Write a verifier in your language. Propose amendments to the draft spec. Contribute reference-implementation modules. No coordination required."
        cta={{ href: "/contribute", label: "Contribute" }}
      />
      <PathCard eyebrow="Volunteers" title="Non-code roles"
        body="Editorial, documentation, design, outreach, operations, domain translation. Subject-matter expertise across law, journalism, audit, and research is especially valued."
        cta={{ href: "/volunteer", label: "Volunteer" }}
      />
      <PathCard eyebrow="Researchers & journalists" title="Adopt the standard"
        body="If your work requires reasoning outputs that survive third-party audit — and your audience must verify without trusting you — Canon is for you."
        cta={{ href: "/meridian-canon", label: "See the implementation" }}
      />
      <PathCard eyebrow="Legal practitioners" title="Flagship use case"
        body="Evidentiary review is the most demanding proving ground for verifiable reasoning. We welcome pilot conversations, amicus collaborations, and practitioner review of the standard."
        cta={{ href: "/partners", label: "Start a conversation" }}
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-ink-200" />

  <!-- ROADMAP -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
    <SectionHeader
      eyebrow="§6 — Current status"
      title="Where we are."
      lede="We publish roadmap honestly. Status language on this site is kept current with the actual state of the work."
    />
    <div class="mt-12">
      <RoadmapTimeline />
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    title="Help us build public infrastructure for verifiable reasoning."
    body="Canon is published. Meridian-Canon is under active construction. Verifier tooling is next. The work is in the open, and it needs support."
    primary={{ href: "/donate", label: "Support the foundation →" }}
    secondary={{ href: "/contribute", label: "Contribute code" }}
  />
</Base>
